:INFO
Setting Up a Mushroom Grow Tent
Setting up a complete mushroom grow tent for home cultivation. Covers tent sizing, humidity and airflow management, lighting, and substrate management for consistent fruiting.

:COUNTER.half
60 to 80 percent
Target relative humidity during colonization
|
:COUNTER.half
90 to 95 percent
Target relative humidity during fruiting

:PATH
Tent Selection and Sizing
A 60x60x140 cm tent fits 4 to 6 fruiting blocks comfortably. Use a tent with multiple vent ports for airflow control. Mylar interiors reflect light and help maintain humidity.

:PATH
Environment Control
Use an ultrasonic humidifier connected to a humidity controller. Set airflow with a small inline fan on a timer. 4 to 6 air exchanges per hour is standard for most gourmet species. Keep temperature between 18 and 24 degrees Celsius.

:PATH
Substrate Management
Prepare substrate outside the tent. Only introduce fully colonized blocks. Remove spent blocks promptly to prevent contamination. Mist walls, not blocks directly.

:CHECKLIST
Tent Setup Checklist
[ ] Tent assembled and all ports sealed or filtered
[ ] Humidifier connected to humidity controller
[ ] Inline fan sized for tent volume
[ ] Thermometer and hygrometer installed
[ ] Light on timer (12 hours on for fruiting cue)
[ ] Drainage tray or liner in place

:NOTE
Contamination is the main challenge in a grow tent. Maintain clean habits when entering the tent: wash hands, work quickly, and never sneeze or cough near fruiting blocks.